- File hierarchy refers to the tree-like structure of file types and their associations; 
- Average interval days is calculated as the difference between the average and minimum Julian dates of user access; 
- The "position in the hierarchy" refers to the level and hierarchy name in the tree-like structure.

- The year 2023 is considered the relevant time frame for accessing the file information; 
- The most accessed file types and formats are determined by the total number of accesses; 
- The most closely associated program is the one with the highest number of associations with each file type and format.

sql:
SELECT format_name, mime_type, created_at
FROM file_formats
ORDER BY created_at DESC;
